		<td valign=top width=452><table cellspacing="4" cellpadding="6" width=100% border=0><tr><td background="/images/newsback.gif"><CENTER><H3><FONT FACE="ARIAL" color="#CB723D">Cruentus Nox</FONT></H3></CENTER>
			
		<b>Level:</b> 5<br>

		<b>Race:</b> Human<br>

		<b>Class:</b> Shadow Knight<br>

		<b>PvP Switch:</b>  On<br>
		
		<center><h4>History:</h4></center>  Chapter One:  The Birth of Cruentus<p>A young woman sits and watches her child as he pours through an ancient manuscript, as he so often does.  Strange that a lad of just 10 years would spend his time alone, rather than playing amongst his peers.  As she sits and watches him, she begins to think back...  She had met his father back when she was just a young girl, only of seventeen years.  He was an evil warlord that had passed through their small town.  She smiles as she remembers the flash of his dark eyes when he saw her waiting tables in her father's tavern.  It was a rare moment of pure rebellion that made her give in to his entreaties to walk by the river alone with him that moonlit night.  All that was left for her to remember that night (besides the child) was his sword.  A dark looking sword with ancient runes carved into the handle and base of the blade.  She had no idea why he had left his sword behind that night and has kept it hidden away in case he should return for it some day.<p>She would later marry a common man who, with her, would raise the child as their own.  As the child matured, they begin to notice that he was much different than the other children of the town.  He seemed somewhat more intense and introspective.  Most of the town folk thought the lad a bit odd at the least and tended to steer clear of him.  These people were the least of the child's worries.  One of the town elders, a high cleric and spiritual leader, had long noticed the dark aura that surrounded the boy.  The cleric knew that something must be done.  This child must not be allowed to reach adulthood.  But the child, having done no wrong to this point, could not simply be killed without a reason.  Or at least not with public knowledge.<p>The eve before the boy's 12th birthday, the cleric pulled the boy's stepfather into his chamber.  The cleric explained his reasoning to the stepfather and detailed a plan as to the boy's murder.  The stepfather was deeply distressed and argued as much as he dared.  But, he was a superstitious man and the cleric was known to be a good and righteous leader, so he reluctantly agreed to the plan.<p>Now, the day of the boy's 12th birthday has come.  After some celebration that morning, the stepfather sneaks the sword from its hiding place (he has long since known she was hiding it, but never questioned her as to its origin) and wraps it tight in a blanket which he slings over his shoulder.  "Naetar", he calls to the boy.  "Now that you are of age, there is something that must be done", he tells the boy.  "Pack a ration of food.. for we have a days travel to our destination".  With their supplies packed, stepfather and son set out on their journey.<p>About a day into their travels, they come to the edge of a dark forest.  After walking about a half mile into this forest, the stepfather stops and says they should set up camp for the night, his voice cracking with the thought of what must be done.  The boy's back now turned to him, he pulls the sword from its makeshift sheath.  With a mighty thrust he drives the sword deep into the boy's back.  The boy slumps over in silence, a pool of blood spreads across the forest floor... surrounding his body.  The forest suddenly seemed threatening.  The stepfather felt malicious eyes on his back, but when he spun to look... nothing was there.  The very air seemed heavy with foreboding as if a circle of evil was spreading... destroying all good that lay in its path.  Distraught, the father runs for the edge of the forest and back to the safe haven of his small town.<p>A few hours later, a band of Dark Elves come riding through the forest and happen upon the boy's body.  Sword still through his middle.  The elves spot the boy's body and approach to investigate.  One of the elves howls out in laughter at the sight of the skewered human corpse.  He rides over to the corpse and pulls at the sword that it might be his.  To the elves' shock as the sword is freed, the boy clenches his left fist closed.  "It's alive!", of of them shouts.  "Haha", another laughs, "let's have some fun with him!"  He tosses the boy's limp body over the back of his horse and remounts.  "Back to the camp!", he hollers.<p>Now back at the Dark Elf camp, they bind the wound through the boy's middle such that he won't die before they've had their fun torturing him.  Tying him to a nearby tree and stripping his blood covered shirt, the elves take turns scarring his back with a whip.  Every lash ebbing a little more of his already fading life.<p>An elder of this dark clan hears the commotion from his quarters and goes to investigate what is so amusing the young warriors.  The dark elder, as the good cleric before him, senses the dark aura surrounding this boy.  "Stop!", he shouts to the young elven warriors as he rushes over to the boy.  Sensing that the boy is nearing death, he has him brought into his private chambers.  Fearing that it is too late for conventional means to save him, the elder calls on the clans most powerful necromancer in  hopes of reviving him.<p>The necromancer arrives and is briefed by the dark elder.  The necromancer examines the boy...  "I cannot raise what is not dead", he tells the elder.  "However, once he is dead, the sooner i bring him back... the more of his soul and being will be returned to him".  The elder agrees to this and the two sit and wait for the boy's life to fade.  Once the breathing had stopped, the necromancer went about his conjuring that he might revive the boy.  After several hours of intense chanting by the necromancer, he becomes very silent and slumps over in exhaustion.  "It is done", he gasps.  "I felt the dark god guide my touch many times.  This one must be very important to our lord."<p>The young boy's body lay motionless on the table still.  His physical being taxed from the experience...  His once black hair now a dead white and his skin from a normal pigment to that of a palish grey, almost white.  The dark elder walks to the table... putting his hand on the boy's chest.  "Arise, my son, Cruentus...  You are home..."  The boy's eyes open...  a dark, cold stare...  The elder looks into his eyes... and can see that any good that had once existed in this boy is forever lost... and this pleases him.
<p><p>
		
